Astra International to Pay 45% of 2010 Profit as Dividend

-- B y   W i d y a   U t a m i
-- 
2011-05-06T04:32:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-06/astra-international-to-pay-45-of-2010-profit-as-dividend-1-.html
PT Astra International,  Indonesia ’s
biggest automotive retailer, will pay a total dividend of 1,600
rupiah a share, or 6.47 trillion rupiah representing 45 percent
of 2010’s net income, the company said in a statement released
in Jakarta today.  The dividend includes an interim dividend of 470 rupiah a
share that was distributed Nov. 15, the statement said. Astra
will distribute the final dividend of 1,130 a share on June 16,
according to the statement.  Astra allocated $1.4 billion for capital expenditure this
year, 40 percent of which will used for expansion of unit PT
United Tractors, the country’s largest seller of heavy equipment,
Astra President Director Prijono Sugiarto said at a press
briefing after the statement was released.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Widya Utami in Jakarta at 
 wutami@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Greg Ahlstrand at 
 gahlstrand@bloomberg.net  